cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.GT

The paper discusses the use of eye tracking for interactive evolution systems, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graphics (cs.GR) for creating 3D printable objects. The use of eye tracking also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for tracking eye movements and improving evolutionary success. Finally, the paper mentions the need for clinical trials, which could involve game theory (cs.GT) for analyzing user behavior and outcomes.
